article.headline: S. Dakota State 38, Cent. Arkansas 10
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Cory Koenig ran for 204 yards and two touchdowns Saturday to lead South Dakota State to a 38-10 win over Central Arkansas. With 21 carries, Koenig averaged nearly 10 yards a carry for the Jackrabbits (5-4). SDSU quarterback Ryan Berry also performed efficiently, completing 14-of-19 passes for 132 yards and two touchdowns, with just one interception. Berry opened the scoring with a pass to Sa. Montague on a play -- the first from scrimmage -- that covered 70 yards. That gave the Jackrabbits a 7-0 lead with 14:46 still left in the first quarter. UCA (5-4) followed with a field goal to narrow the gap, then took a 10-7 lead on a 1-yard run by Ceasar Leonard on the first play of the second period. From there, it was all SDSU, with Koenig scoring on two 1-yard runs, Kyle Minnett on a 16-yard run, Chris Wagner on a 2-yard pass from Berry, and Parker Douglass with a 36-yard field goal. UCA quarterback completed 29-of-36 passing attempts, but was intercepted three times and sacked 5 times.
